'''Nikaidō Shrine''' (にかいどうじんじゃ) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located on the site of [[Sukagawa Castle]] in [[Sukagawa City]], [[Fukushima Prefecture]]. It enshrines the [[Nikaidō clan]], the lords of the castle.
The "{{ill|Taimatsu Akashi|ja|松明あかし|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taimatsu Akashi|qq=}}" fire festival, which is considered one of "Japan’s Three Great Fire Festivals," takes the sacred fire from this shrine every November. The fire is carried throughout Sukagawa City and brought to the venue at Midorigaoka Park<ref>[https://www.tif.ne.jp/jp/spot.html?spot=1736 Nikaidō Shrine]</ref><ref>[https://www.sukagawa-kankoukyoukai.jp/learn/page04.html Nikaidō Shrine]</ref>. A large zelkova tree on the shrine grounds is designated as a natural monument of Sukagawa City.
